# 4. 少年とトランペット

Announcement: <That concludes this concert. Please watch your step and make sure to take all of your belongings with you.>
Kanade: Phew... That was a nice concert.
Kanade: I wasn't expecting to see ten different groups perform... The bands that played only Japanese instruments or traditional instruments from around the world gave me a chance to hear plenty of music that I normally wouldn't.
Mafuyu: You seem to be really enjoying things, Kanade.
Kanade: Oh, I can't help it... It's just been so long since I got to listen to a live performance.
Kanade: What did you think, Mafuyu?
Mafuyu: I thought it was good.
Kanade: I see...
Kanade: (I'm glad this is turning into a nice distraction for her.)
Kanade: Anyway, what should we do now? The instrument booths and such all still seem to be open.
Kanade: Whoa!
Mafuyu: Are you okay, Kanade?
Kanade: Y-Yes. But I bumped into something just now.
Boy: Oh... I-I'm sorry...
Kanade: I-I'm also sorry. I should've paid more attention to where I was going...
Boy: N-No, it was my fault for...
Boy: *Wince*
Kanade: (Is something wrong? He looks like he's about to cry.)
Kanade: A-Are you okay? Did you get hurt somewhere when we bumped into each other just now?
Boy: N-No, I'm not hurt. I'm sorry... It's just...
Kanade: Huh? Wh-What's wrong?
Boy: Uhh... ...
Kanade: Umm...
Kanade: (H-He's gone silent... But we can't just leave him here like this.)
Kanade: F-For now, why don't we go take a seat over on that bench?
Mafuyu: Good idea. That should give you a chance to settle down.
Kanade: H-How does that sound?
Boy: Okay...
Boy: Thank you very much.
Kanade: You're welcome. Anyway, shall we?
Boy: I'm really sorry... I didn't mean to cause you two so much trouble.
Kanade: No, that's okay.
Kanade: But you still haven't told us what's wrong. Did you get lost?
Boy: N-No, I'm not lost! It's just...
Boy: It's just...
Boy: I'm so frustrated...
Mafuyu: Frustrated?
Boy: So, I'm in a marching band. I play the trumpet...
Boy: But I'm always having trouble, and making weird sounds. Because of that, I end up getting left out of performances...
Boy: Then, I saw all those people during today's concert sound really cool while playing their trumpets...
Boy: I got so jealous... And frustrated. I started wondering why I'm so bad and they're so good...
Kanade: I see...
Boy: Why am I so bad?
Boy: I really want to learn how to play beautiful music like them...
Kanade: ...
Kanade: (“Like them”...)
Kanade: (I sort of understand how he feels.)
Kanade: (I also wanted to learn to play like Dad.)
Kanade: (I wish I could do something to help this boy...)
Kanade: (But I don't know how to play the trumpet. What do I do in this situation?)
Mafuyu: Come to think of it, the booth for wind instruments seems to have a demo area.
Mafuyu: The people there may be able to teach you how to produce the sound you want.
Boy: What...?
Kanade: Oh, that's right. That booth does seem to have teachers or instructors available for help.
Kanade: So, are you free right now? Unless you need to leave soon...
Boy: No, actually... We have free time to look around until the end of the convention.
Kanade: Really? Then, why don't you try visiting that demo area?
Boy: Oh...
Boy: B-But I still probably won't be able to play very well... I've already tried doing so many different things...
Kanade: Yes, that may be true.
Kanade: However, if you keep trying, then I'm sure you'll eventually figure out a way.
Kanade: You don't have to if you really don't want to, but I think you should give this a chance.
Mafuyu: ...
Mafuyu: If you don't feel comfortable going all by yourself, then we'll join you.
Boy: ...
Boy: Thank you very much. I'll give it a try!
Kanade: ...!
Kanade: Good! Then, shall we?
Boy: Let's go!!
